ProMED-mail Rapporteurs Mary Marshall and Kunihiko Iizuka

- Thu 31 Jan 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=b6ba7cc34f

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 30 Jan 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 759, of which 705 are confirmed and 54 are probable. In total, there were 468 deaths (414 confirmed and 54 probable) and 259 people cured.
- 178 suspected cases are under investigation.
- 7 new confirmed cases, including 6 in Katwa and 1 in Butembo.
- 3 new deaths of confirmed cases, including 1 community death in Katwa and 2 deaths at CTE, including 1 in Butembo and 1 in Katwa

News of the response
- The Ebola treatment center (ETC) of Kayina, consisting of 8 beds, opened this Wed 30 Jan 2019. This is the 10th CTE built after those of Beni, Bunia, Butembo, Goma, Katwa, Komanda, Mandima, Mangina, and Tchomia.

Vaccination
---------
- More than 70 000 people [70 611] were vaccinated in 28 health zones, spread among 4 provinces of the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC).

