[Each new Ebola treatment center is an important step towards protecting the population and the healthcare workers alike. One can see how they become filled quickly, since there are only 8 beds for patients. However, that may be better than a large facility, as it may be less intimidating to the community, as discussed in the New York Times OpEd piece (ProMED-mail Ebola update (12): Congo DR (NK, IT) cases, summaries, preparedness, treatment 20190131.6287934). - Mod.LK]

